-- Hungary's Planned Tax Changes in 2010 Will Improve Budget, Council Says
-- Balazs Penz
-- 2010-07-07T07:48:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/hungary-s-planned-tax-changes-in-2010-will-improve-budget-council-says.html

          
          
             Hungary’s planned tax changes,
including a new levy on the financial industry and reductions in
the corporate income tax rate, will improve this year’s budget
balance by about 80 billion forint ($353 million), the Fiscal
Council said in an e-mail today.  
          
          


  


        